article_title: Affordable Care Act Enrollment Near 10 Million
article_text:
WASHINGTON—Almost 10 million people have signed up for health insurance in state and federal marketplaces under the Affordable Care Act or were re-enrolled in coverage for 2015, federal officials said Wednesday.

Nearly 7.5 million people have selected a plan or were automatically re-enrolled on the federal exchange, Sylvia Mathews Burwell, secretary of Health and Human Services, said at a Senate hearing. At least 2.4 million people...
